GLOSSARY
Fully open: no joints of selected fingers are flexed
Bent (closed): non-base joints are flexed
Flat-open: base joints flexed less than 90¼
Flat-closed: base joints flexed equal to or more that 90¼
Curved open: base and non-base joints flexed without contact
Curved closed: base and non-base joints flexed with contact
Fully closed: base and non-base joints fully flexed
Stacked: Flexion of selected fingers differs
